Added Handling Auth Errors (#13)

* Added ASGIAPPError

Basically the same as ASGIAPP type with the addition of an Exception parameter

* Added default_401 function

Default error handler for on_auth_error

* Added on_auth_error to RateLimitMiddleware

All exceptions from RateLimitMiddleware.authenticate are send to RateLimitMiddleware.on_auth_error and __call__ returns after that

* Added one test for missing auth

Test sends a request with empty headers to make sure the EmptyInformation exception is handled by on_auth_error and a 401 status code is returned

* Leave handling auth error to user

on_auth_error will be None by default and will raise the exception in the auth function. If user provides a on_auth_error parameter, it will be called and its reponse returned

* Remove ASGIAppError

It's not needed anymore

* Remove added test form test_redis

* Added tests to test_core.py

Includes tests for 200 response, raising exceptions by default, returning 401 based on user-defined on_auth_error and etc
